        LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_RE_LIGHT_ON_FUNDS_KUPO                                = 6687,  -- Looks like you're light on funds, kupo... Sorry!
        WHAT_S_THIS_YOU_RE_STILL_NEW_TO                                      = 6688,  -- What's this? You're still new to this land? I'm afraid you're not yet strong enough to handle our potent moogle magic! Just forget I said anything, kupo!
        OH_WHAT_A_SHAME_THE_MOG_TABLETS_HAVE                                 = 6689,  -- Oh, what a shame! The mog tablets have been scattered to the winds once more! Without their power, I'm afraid we can't help you, kupo.
        HELLO_THERE_IS_THIS_YOUR_FIRST_VISIT_TO                              = 6690,  -- Hello there. Is this your first visit to our fine town?
        WELL_IS_IT_WHY_YES_NO_I_COME                                         = 6691,  -- Well, is it? Why, yes. No, I come here all the time.
        YES_I_THOUGHT_AS_MUCH_YOU_D_BEST                                     = 6692,  -- Yes, I thought as much. You'd best head to the mayor's office.
        TROT_DOWN_TOWARDS_THE_SHORE_AND_TAKE_THE                             = 6693,  -- Trot down towards the shore and take the first stairway. Turn right, follow the wall, and there it will be.
        IS_THAT_A_FACT_I_NEVER_FORGET_A                                      = 6694,  -- Is that a fact? I never forget a face. Oh well. Never mind.
        HAVE_YOU_BEEN_TO_SEE_THE_MAYOR_IF                                    = 6695,  -- Have you been to see the mayor? If not, you should!
        WELL_WELL_NICE_TO_SEE_A_NEW_FACE                                     = 6696,  -- Well, well. Nice to see a new face. This your first time to Selbina?
        OH_I_THINK_YOU_SHOULD_GO_SEE_THE                                     = 6697,  -- Oh. I think you should go see the mayor.
        HIS_OFFICE_IS_WAY_OVER_ON_THE_WEST                                   = 6698,  -- His office is way over on the west side of town, atop the tallest hill.
        OH_BY_THE_WAY_IT_S_A_GOOD                                            = 6699,  -- Oh. By the way, it's a good idea to show your face to our mayor if you still haven't.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_MAYOR_S_RESIDENCE_HOW_CAN                             = 6700,  -- Welcome to the mayor's residence. How can I help you?
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_THIS                               = 6701,  -- What would you like to know? About this town. About the shops and services here. Nothing.
        I_CAN_TELL_YOU_MUCH_ABOUT_SELBINA                                    = 6702,  -- I can tell you much about Selbina.
        WHICH_SUBJECT_INTERESTS_YOU_HISTORY_GEOGRAPHY_INDUSTRY_THAT          = 6703,  -- Which subject interests you? History. Geography. Industry. That's enough.
        VERY_WELL_SELBINA_WAS_ESTABLISHED_BY_BASTOK_AS                       = 6704,  -- Very well. Selbina was established by Bastok as a haven for ships bearing Gustaberg ore. She soon grew into a thriving port town.
        SELBINA_DECLARED_NEUTRALITY_AT_THE_OUTBREAK_OF_THE                   = 6705,  -- Selbina declared neutrality at the outbreak of the Great War and maintains her independence to this day.
        VERY_WELL_OUR_FAIR_TOWN_LIES_IN_THE                                  = 6706,  -- Very well. Our fair town lies in the middle of Valkurm Dunes, here in central Quon.
        MOST_OF_THE_COASTLINE_CONSISTS_OF_DUNES_AND                          = 6707,  -- Most of the coastline consists of dunes and shallows. Selbina stands atop the only suitable harbor.
        VERY_WELL_THANKS_TO_THE_HARBOR_INDUSTRY_IN                           = 6708,  -- Very well. Thanks to the harbor, industry in Selbina has prospered throughout the ages.
        BUT_AIRSHIPS_ARE_THE_WAVE_OF_THE_FUTURE                              = 6709,  -- But airships are the wave of the future, so we are trying to develop local industries such as fishing and agriculture.
        VERY_WELL_HERE_WE_HAVE_REGIONAL_SALESROOMS_OF                        = 6710,  -- Very well. Here we have regional salesrooms of the Fishermen's and Weavers' Guilds, as well as an inn and the sea travel agency.
        YOU_CAN_PURCHASE_WEAPONS_FROM_TORAPIONT_INSIDE_THE                   = 6711,  -- You can purchase weapons from Torapiont inside the inn, and local items from Dohdjuma in front of the warehouse.
        PLEASE_COME_BACK_IF_YOU_HAVE_ANY_QUESTIONS                           = 6712,  -- Please come back if you have any questions. Good day.
        ANOTHER_ADVENTURER_IN_SELBINA_I_DON_T_KNOW                           = 6713,  -- Another adventurer in Selbina? I don't know where you come from, but you must be quite resourceful to make it this far out.
        THESE_DAYS_FOLKS_LIKE_YOU_SPEND_EVERY_HARD                           = 6714,  -- These days, folks like you spend every hard-earned gil on shiny new weapons and armor.
        AND_THEN_THEY_JUST_TOSS_OUT_THEIR_OLD                                = 6715,  -- And then they just toss out their old onion-gear as if it were rubbish!
        WHY_MY_FATHER_ALWAYS_SCOLDED_ME_WHENEVER_I                           = 6716,  -- Why, my father always scolded me whenever I left trash about! Indeed, a true adventurer would not litter, and neither should you!
        THAT_S_WHY_I_THOUGHT_OF_A_PLAN                                       = 6717,  -- That's why I thought of a plan: I'd gather old, worn-out onion equipment and recycle them.
        THAT_S_WHERE_YOU_COME_IN_BRING_ME                                    = 6718,  -- That's where you come in! Bring me five pieces of onion equipment, and I'll reward you for your efforts.
        YES_THESE_WILL_DO_NICELY_TAKE_THIS_AS                                = 6719,  -- Yes, these will do nicely! Take this as a token of my thanks.
        REMEMBER_NEVER_JUST_THROW_ANYTHING_AWAY_THERE_IS                     = 6720,  -- Remember, never just throw anything away. There is always a use for things!
        NOW_ONCE_I_GET_THESE_LITTLE_ONIONS_MENDED                            = 6721,  -- Now, once I get these little onions mended and polished, I'll send them off for sale abroad. I'm sure new recruits will find them useful.
        OH_SORRY_I_WAS_LOST_IN_THOUGHT                                       = 6722,  -- Oh, sorry... I was lost in thought.
        AS_YOU_VE_NO_DOUBT_DISCOVERED_THIS_HERE                              = 6723,  -- As you've no doubt discovered, this here village owes its life to the fish. Bless their hearts...
        SAY_DID_YOU_HEAR_OSWALD_THAT_TRAVELING_MERCHANT                      = 6724,  -- Say, did you hear? Oswald, that traveling merchant... He said he lost a ring out in the harbor some time ago.
        OF_COURSE_I_VE_HEARD_THE_NEWS_HE                                     = 6725,  -- Of course I've heard the news. He said it was so precious to him, his face turned blue!
        YES_POOR_CHAP_IT_MUST_BE_AT_THE                                      = 6726,  -- Yes...poor chap! It must be at the bottom of the sea by now. I feel awful for him, but he'll never see it again.
        DON_T_MIND_ME_I_HAVE_A_LOT                                           = 6727,  -- Don't mind me. I have a lot to think about and... Huh? Oh, you've heard about my ring, have you?
        I_DROPPED_IT_NEAR_THE_PIER_AND_IT                                    = 6728,  -- I dropped it near the pier and it just... It was so dear to me. I don't know what to do.
        I_D_GIVE_ANYTHING_TO_GET_MY_RING                                     = 6729,  -- I'd give anything to get my ring back. Anything! But the ocean has swallowed it forever. It's lost.
        WHAT_YOU_WANT_ME_TO_LOOK_FOR_A                                       = 6730,  -- What!? You want me to look for a ring? Oh, my! You ask the impossible.
        OSWALD_S_RING_EH_I_D_SURE_LIKE                                       = 6731,  -- Oswald's ring, eh? I'd sure like to help him out, but there's no way I could find a ring on the bottom of the sea.
        WAIT_MAYBE_ZALDON_KNOWS_SOMETHING_THAT_OLD_ANGLER                    = 6732,  -- Wait! Maybe Zaldon knows something. That old angler's the most knowledgeable man in this here whole village.
        WHAT_YOU_RE_OUT_TO_FIND_THAT_RING                                    = 6733,  -- What? You're out to find that ring? That's like finding a needle in a haystack!
        HMM_OF_COURSE_IT_S_NOT_IMPOSSIBLE_BUT                                = 6734,  -- Hmm... Of course, it's not impossible. But I wouldn't get my hopes up too high.
        LISTEN_AROUND_HERE_THE_OFTEN_BITE_HECK_THEY                          = 6735,  -- Listen. Around here, the % often bite. Heck, they'll swallow anything that sparkles.
        THERE_S_A_CHANCE_THAT_ONE_OF_THEM                                    = 6736,  -- There's a chance that one of them gulped the ring down. So, catch as many % as you can, and you just might find it!
        THERE_S_NO_GUARANTEE_YOU_LL_GET_IT                                   = 6737,  -- There's no guarantee you'll get it, but what have you got to lose? It beats scouring the bottom of the sea, doesn't it?
        ONCE_YOU_CATCH_BRING_IT_I_LL_CUT                                     = 6738,  -- Once you catch %, bring it. I'll cut it open for you.
        CAUGHT_ONE_DID_YOU_WELL_GIVE_ME_A                                    = 6739,  -- Caught one, did you? Well, give me a second here. I'll cut it right open.
        OH_TOO_BAD_NO_RING_IN_THIS_HERE                                      = 6740,  -- Oh, too bad. No ring in this here fish. You must catch more.
        WELL_TUG_MY_TAIL_I_NEVER_THOUGHT_YOU                                 = 6741,  -- Well, tug my tail! I never thought you'd find it, but here it is!
        HERE_YOU_GO_THAT_S_SOME_FINE_FISHERMANSHIP                           = 6742,  -- Here you go! That's some fine fishermanship, I must say! Make sure that fool Oswald never drops it again!
        YES_WHAT_IS_THIS_GOODNESS_GRACIOUS_MY_RING                           = 6743,  -- Yes, what is this? Goodness gracious! My ring! You found my precious ring! Thank you! Thank you so much!
        YOU_SEE_THIS_IS_AN_ENGAGEMENT_RING_MY                                = 6744,  -- You see, this is an engagement ring. My love dwells in Mhaura, and someday I shall offer this to her.
        HOW_COULD_I_FORGET_MY_PROMISE_THIS_IS                                = 6745,  -- How could I forget my promise? This is but a mere token of my thanks, but take it; you've more than earned it!
        HALLO_THERE_WHIT_DAE_YE_THINK_OF_MA                                  = 6746,  -- Hallo there. Whit dae ye think of ma sheep? Ah uised tae chaise doon wild yins fer their wuil, but nou ah've got sheep of ma ain!
        ASIDES_YE_NEED_HEALTHY_SHEEP_TAE_GET_QUALITY                         = 6747,  -- Asides, ye need healthy sheep tae get quality wuil! An ah anlie want the verra best!
        THA_S_WHY_AH_STAIRTED_RAISIN_SHEEP_MASEL                             = 6748,  -- Tha's why ah stairted raisin sheep masel!
        MA_FAMILY_MINDS_THE_SHOP_FER_ME_SAE                                  = 6749,  -- Ma family minds the shop fer me, sae ah can stay oot here an watch ower ma sheep.
        BUT_GETTIN_QUALITY_WUIL_IS_AWFIE_HAIRD                               = 6750,  -- But gettin quality wuil is awfie haird!
        SAE_AH_M_ETTLIN_TAE_STUFF_THEM_WI                                    = 6751,  -- Sae ah'm ettlin tae stuff them wi the verra best feed!
        THA_S_WHY_AH_NEED_YER_HELP_LADDIE                                    = 6752,  -- Tha's why ah need yer help, laddie/lass]. Would ye mind fetchin me some feed fer ma sheep?
        WELL_OF_COURSE_SORRY_BUT_I_CAN_T                                     = 6753,  -- Well? Of course. Sorry, but I can't.
        YE_WILL_THA_S_A_BRAW_LAD_GOOD                                        = 6754,  -- Ye will? Tha's a braw lad/good lass]! Ah'm needin many different sorts of them, an some mair than ithers. Listen cannily!
        AH_NEED_FIVE                                                         = 6755,  -- Ah need five %.
        ALSAE_AH_COULD_UISE_THREE                                            = 6756,  -- Alsae, ah could uise three %.
        LASTLY_AH_COULD_UISE_JIST_ONE_MIND_AN                                = 6757,  -- Lastly, ah could uise jist one %. Mind an caw cannie!
        BRAW_WIRK_LAD_LASSIE_YE_VE_BROUGHT_ME                                = 6758,  -- Braw wirk, lad/lassie]. Ye've brought me these %, have ye? Here, take this wi ma thanks!
        MA_SHEEP_ARE_AYE_IN_NEED_OF_QUALITY                                  = 6759,  -- Ma sheep are aye in need of quality feed. Anytime ye find some, bring it ower, an ah'll take it right awa.
        OCH_YE_FORGOT_WHIT_SORTAY_FEED_AH_M                                  = 6760,  -- Och, ye forgot whit sortay feed ah'm needin, did ye? Well, here it is agane, sae listen cannily!
        NAEBODY_S_IVVER_TELT_ME_NAE_GOT_OWER                                 = 6761,  -- Naebody's ivver telt me nae! Got ower muckle oan yer hauns, have ye? Come back aroon anytime. Ah'll be right here.
        I_M_ABELARD_MAYOR_OF_THIS_VILLAGE_IT                                 = 6762,  -- I'm Abelard, mayor of this village. It's so tiny, you see, that all I do is mediate when there are disagreements.
        IN_MY_SPARE_TIME_I_RESEARCH_THE_LIFE                                 = 6763,  -- In my spare time I research the life of Gwynham, the man who charted the maps we all carry today.
        HE_WAS_AN_ADVENTURER_LIKE_YOU_HIS_TRAVELS                            = 6764,  -- He was an adventurer, like you. His travels took him far and wide, and slowly he fleshed out his maps.
        ONE_DAY_I_DISCOVERED_THAT_STONE_MONUMENTS_BEARING                    = 6765,  -- One day I discovered that stone monuments bearing his words lie in various places all over the world.
        IT_SEEMS_EACH_MONUMENT_CARRIES_A_DIFFERENT_QUOTE                     = 6766,  -- It seems each monument carries a different quote. I'd love to rush out there and see them all, but it's tough at my age.
        SAY_MAYBE_YOU_COULD_HELP_ME_GATHER_HIS                               = 6767,  -- Say, maybe you could help me gather his words! Well, what do you say?
        WHAT_A_RELIEF_WELL_THERE_S_NO_TIME                                   = 6768,  -- What a relief! Well, there's no time to lose! Let's get you started on one close by.
        TAKE_THIS_CLAY_TO_THE_MONUMENT_IN_WEST                               = 6769,  -- Take this clay to the monument in West Ronfaure, and press it firmly upon the inscription. Then, bring it back so I can print a copy for my collection.
        NOBODY_SEEMS_TO_KNOW_EXACTLY_WHERE_TO_FIND                           = 6770,  -- Nobody seems to know exactly where to find the monument, so I suppose it might be difficult to find. Take care!
        IS_THAT_RIGHT_WELL_THAT_S_TOO_BAD                                    = 6771,  -- Is that right? Well, that's too bad. Come back if you ever have a change of heart.
        AT_LAST_YOU_VE_DONE_IT_YOU_HAVE                                      = 6772,  -- At last! You've done it! You have my warmest thanks. Here, this is a reward for your effort. Don't expect too much from this old man, though, hehe.
        AH_YOU_RE_BACK_THIS_ISN_T_THE                                        = 6773,  -- Ah, you're back! This isn't the one I asked for, but beggars can't be choosers! Here, it's not much, but take this.
        WELL_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_BRING_BACK_ANOTHER                               = 6774,  -- Well? Do you want to bring back another one for me?
        ACTUALLY_I_DON_T_KNOW_WHERE_THE_OTHERS                               = 6775,  -- Actually, I don't know where the others are. You'll have to find them and make the impressions yourself. Good luck, and take care!
        HELLO_AGAIN_HOW_S_IT_GOING_GOT_THE                                   = 6776,  -- Hello again! How's it going? Got the guts to go out and search for monuments yet? Sometimes they're a cakewalk, you know. What do you say?
        WHAT_HOW_COULD_YOU_LOSE_A_BIG_PIECE                                  = 6777,  -- What? How could you lose a big piece of clay!? Here, I'll give you another one. Now, take care!
        OH_I_M_SORRY_MY_FRIEND_BUT_I                                         = 6778,  -- Oh, I'm sorry, my friend, but I've already got this one, so try getting me a different one. Take care, now.
        YOU_DON_T_KNOW_WHERE_TO_GO_NEXT                                      = 6779,  -- You don't know where to go next, eh? Well, I still don't have an impression from the monument in [West Ronfaure/East Ronfaure/La Theine/Valkurm/Jugner Forest/Batallia/North Gustaberg/South Gustaberg/Konschtat], you know.
        YOU_DON_T_KNOW_WHERE_TO_GO_NEXT_2                                    = 6780,  -- You don't know where to go next, eh? Well, I still don't have an impression from the monument in [Pashhow/Rolanberry/West Sarutabaruta/East Sarutabaruta/Tahrongi Canyon/Buburimu/Meriphataud/Sauromugue], you know.
        YOU_RE_BACK_AND_WITH_THE_LAST_ONE                                    = 6781,  -- You're back! And with the last one! Thank you so much, my friend. In return for your unwavering kindness, I give you this.
        WELL_IT_S_GOOD_TO_SEE_YOU_AGAIN                                      = 6782,  -- Well, it's good to see you again! My research is going quite well, thanks to you. I hope that map's been useful.
        YEAH_WHO_THE_HECK_ARE_YOU_IF_YOU                                     = 6783,  -- Yeah? Who the heck are you? If you wanna be somebody, get some more experience under your belt!
        WE_WORK_THE_DOCKS_LOADING_THE_SHIPS_WITH                             = 6784,  -- We work the docks, loading the ships with cargo. You know, ships can't sail without food and water, but they take up precious cargo space.
        SO_LONG_AGO_ONE_SEA_DOG_HAD_AN                                       = 6785,  -- So, long ago one sea dog had an idea. He figured that % are loaded with water and nutrition. He could kill two birds with one stone.
        THE_THING_WAS_REGULAR_DIDN_T_WORK_HE                                 = 6786,  -- The thing was, regular % didn't work! He needed the ones crawlers like to hoard in their nests. The more aged, the better!
        IF_YOU_EVER_GET_YOUR_HANDS_ON_SOME                                   = 6787,  -- If you ever get your hands on some %, bring them on back to me here. And the older they are, the more I'll pay!
        HEY_THANKS_A_LOT_BRING_ME_ALL_YOU                                    = 6788,  -- Hey, thanks a lot. Bring me all you find; there's more gil where that came from!
        I_M_A_LITTLE_SHORT_ON_GIL_AT                                         = 6789,  -- I'm a little short on gil at the moment. I'll buy your % once my wages come in...
        HELLO_HOW_HAVE_YOU_BEEN_HAVEN_T_SEEN                                 = 6790,  -- Hello, how have you been? Haven't seen you for some time.
        ME_YES_I_M_DOING_FINE_THANKS_BUT                                     = 6791,  -- Me? Yes, I'm doing fine, thanks. But my girlfriend's just not feeling well at all.
        I_DON_T_THINK_SHE_S_SICK_SO                                          = 6792,  -- I don't think she's sick, so I'm just having her eat nutritious things and hoping she starts feeling better soon.
        I_ASKED_THE_COOK_AT_THE_INN_FOR                                      = 6793,  -- I asked the cook at the inn for some help. He said he'd need some special ingredients, but there's no way I could get them!
        YOU_HELPED_ME_OUT_SO_MUCH_BEFORE_SO                                  = 6794,  -- You helped me out so much before, so maybe you could do just one more favor for me.
        THANK_YOU_VERY_MUCH_HE_WANTED                                        = 6795,  -- Thank you very much. He wanted %.
        THEY_SAY_THEY_RE_REALLY_HARD_TO_COME                                 = 6796,  -- They say they're really hard to come by. Take care, and best of luck to you.
        IS_THAT_A_FACT_I_WONDER_WHO_COULD                                    = 6797,  -- Is that a fact? I wonder who could have the time to help me...
        SAY_THIS_IS_YOU_FOUND_IT_YOU_REALLY                                  = 6798,  -- Say, this is %! You found it. You really found it! Thank you so much! Now he can start on that dish!
        THIS_IS_ALL_I_HAVE_TO_GIVE_PLEASE                                    = 6799,  -- This is all I have to give. Please, take it. You're our savior!
        OH_HELLO_THERE_THANKS_FOR_HELPING_ME_OUT                             = 6800,  -- Oh, hello there. Thanks for helping me out then. My girlfriend was very grateful.
        BUT_SHE_STILL_ISN_T_BACK_TO_HER                                      = 6801,  -- But she still isn't back to her old self. So, I started thinking some more...
        I_THOUGHT_THAT_MAYBE_THE_REAL_CULPRIT_IS                             = 6802,  -- I thought that maybe the real culprit is food itself! Once you eat something, it's gone, right?
        AND_THAT_S_WHEN_I_CAME_UP_WITH                                       = 6803,  -- And that's when I came up with this great idea for my next present...but I'll need a little help getting it.
        WELL_WHAT_DO_YOU_SAY_COULD_I_CALL                                    = 6804,  -- Well, what do you say? Could I call upon you for yet another favor?
        OH_I_SEE_BUT_I_REALLY_WOULD_PREFER                                   = 6805,  -- Oh, I see. But I really would prefer you! If you ever find the time to help me, please come back.
        I_KNOW_I_MIGHT_SEEM_STUBBORN_BUT_YOU                                 = 6806,  -- I know I might seem stubborn, but you're my only hope.
        I_HEARD_ABOUT_HOW_YOU_FOUND_THE_RING                                 = 6807,  -- I heard about how you found the ring. You caught so many fish, and finally you found it inside one of them, right?
        WELL_SINCE_YOU_RE_SUCH_A_FINE_FISHERMAN                              = 6808,  -- Well, since you're such a fine fisherman, I wanted to ask you to find % for me.
        THEY_SAY_THAT_YIELD_PEARLS_IF_I_FIND                                 = 6809,  -- They say that % yield pearls. If I find one, I'm planning on having a boneworker fix it up for me.
        THEN_I_COULD_GIVE_MY_GIRLFRIEND_A_FINE                               = 6810,  -- Then I could give my girlfriend a fine pearl necklace. Well, don't you think she'd like it?
        BUT_WITHOUT_I_CAN_T_EVEN_BEGIN_I                                     = 6811,  -- But without %, I can't even begin. I wish I knew where they could be caught. If I knew someone who could tell me.
        I_HAVE_A_FEELING_YOU_LL_FIGURE_SOMETHING                             = 6812,  -- I have a feeling you'll figure something out. Please, do what you can.
        NOW_WHAT_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_DON_T                                    = 6813,  -- Now what? You're looking for %? Don't you have anything better to do?
        I_HEAR_YOU_CAN_FIND_IN_SANDY_PLACES                                  = 6814,  -- I hear you can find % in sandy places like Valkurm and Buburimu. Heck, get a chocobo to dig some up on the coast.
        LEMME_GUESS_YOU_WANT_TO_GET_SOME_PEARLS                              = 6815,  -- Lemme guess. You want to get some pearls from the %, right? Well, it takes time, but it's a lot cheaper than buying them.
        GOODNESS_YOU_FOUND_ONE_THANK_YOU_SO_MUCH                             = 6816,  -- Goodness, you found one! Thank you so much! Here, this is for you.
        YOU_RE_SO_FANTASTIC_MY_GIRLFRIEND_AND_I                              = 6817,  -- You're so fantastic! My girlfriend and I thank you from the bottom of our hearts.
        OH_HELLO_AGAIN_THANKS_FOR_ALL_YOU_VE                                 = 6818,  -- Oh, hello again. Thanks for all you've done. My girlfriend was quite impressed with the necklace! The thing is, she said something rather odd.
        SHE_SAID_THANKS_FOR_THE_GIFT_BUT_WHAT                                = 6819,  -- She said, Thanks for the gift, but what I want the most is you here next to me.
        I_DIDN_T_KNOW_WHAT_TO_SAY_NOBODY                                     = 6820,  -- I didn't know what to say. Nobody's ever said such things to me!
        THANKS_TO_YOU_I_FEEL_LIKE_I_VE                                       = 6821,  -- Thanks to you, I feel like I've learned what's really important.
        NOW_I_KNOW_THAT_SHE_S_THE_ONE                                        = 6822,  -- Now I know that she's the one. Thank you so much for all the help!
        OH_HELLO_AGAIN_I_CAN_T_BELIEVE_I                                     = 6823,  -- Oh, hello again. I can't believe I ever lost that ring. I won't let that happen again.
        THESE_DAYS_WE_TRAVELING_MERCHANTS_FIGHT_FOR_OUR                      = 6824,  -- These days we traveling merchants fight for our survival. But we can't just give up our livelihood. After all, things weren't always like this.
        I_VE_BEEN_ALL_OVER_VANA_DIEL_BUT                                     = 6825,  -- I've been all over Vana'diel, but the inn here is my favorite. It's not the most luxurious place in the world, but I love the relaxed atmosphere.
        I_HEAR_ABOUT_YOU_A_LOT_PEOPLE_SAY                                    = 6826,  -- I hear about you a lot. People say you do much for Selbina.
        I_SPEAK_FOR_THE_WHOLE_TOWN_WHEN_I                                    = 6827,  -- I speak for the whole town when I say thank you. Thank you.
        THING_IS_THE_TURTLEBACKS_ARE_ON_THE_MOVE                             = 6828,  -- Thing is, the turtlebacks are on the move. Word is they're up to no good.
        I_M_ITCHING_TO_GO_SMASH_THEM_BUT                                     = 6829,  -- I'm itching to go smash them, but I can't leave the town defenseless.
        MAYBE_YOU_COULD_GO_INSTEAD_WHAT_DO_YOU                               = 6830,  -- Maybe you could go instead. What do you say?
        THANKS_THE_TURTLEBACKS_OFTEN_STRIKE_MERCHANTS_HEADED_TO              = 6831,  -- Thanks. The turtlebacks often strike merchants headed to our village. Another caravan was attacked just the other day.
        THEY_FLED_BUT_TWO_OF_THEM_WERE_TAKEN                                 = 6832,  -- They fled, but two of them were taken prisoner.
        THE_TURTLEBACKS_PROWLING_OUTSIDE_CAME_FROM_BEADEAUX_WE               = 6833,  -- The turtlebacks prowling outside came from Beadeaux. We think the merchants are held captive there.
        THEIR_NAMES_ARE_EVRARD_AND_SERAFIN                                   = 6834,  -- Their names are Evrard and Serafin.
        THEY_SAY_THAT_THE_TURTLEBACKS_KEEP_PRISONERS_LOCKED                  = 6835,  -- They say that the turtlebacks keep prisoners locked up tight. Somewhere in Beadeaux there should be such a place.
        THE_MERCHANTS_WHO_MADE_IT_HERE_SAID_THAT                             = 6836,  -- The merchants who made it here said that they were different from other turtlebacks. I hope that helps.
        I_HATE_ASKING_OTHERS_TO_DO_OUR_JOB                                   = 6837,  -- I hate asking others to do our job, but please, rescue the two captives. Their families need them.
        OH_PITY_I_HOPED_YOU_WOULD_SAY_YES                                    = 6838,  -- Oh? Pity... I hoped you would say yes.
        W_WE_RE_SAVED_I_THOUGHT_THEY_WERE                                    = 6839,  -- W-we're saved! I thought they were going to kill us! Thank you!
        PLEASE_TAKE_OUR_THINGS_BACK_TO_SELBINA_FOR                           = 6840,  -- Please, take our things back to Selbina for us. We can run well enough on our own.
        WE_RE_SO_GLAD_YOU_CAME_AS_LONG                                       = 6841,  -- We're so glad you came. As long as you carry our packs for us, we can watch the enemy as we make our way to safety.
        ONCE_BACK_IN_SELBINA_GIVE_OUR_PACKS_TO                               = 6842,  -- Once back in Selbina, give our packs to Thunder Hawk. He'll make sure we get them. Thank you, brave one!
        AH_PERFECT_WE_JUST_ARRIVED_AS_WELL                                   = 6843,  -- Ah, perfect! We just arrived as well.
        WHEW_I_M_SO_GLAD_WE_RE_FREE                                          = 6844,  -- Whew, I'm so glad we're free! We owe our lives to you!
        WE_RE_THANKFUL_ENOUGH_YOU_RE_SAFE_WE                                 = 6845,  -- We're thankful enough you're safe. We apologize we couldn't help you.
        BUT_YOU_DID_WELL_THANK_YOU_THIS_IS                                   = 6846,  -- But you did well. Thank you! This is for your service.
        YOU_SAVED_OUR_LIVES_FRIEND_LET_US_THANK                              = 6847,  -- You saved our lives, friend! Let us thank you as well. Here, take this!
        OH_IT_S_YOU_AGAIN_THERE_IS_NOTHING                                   = 6848,  -- Oh, it's you again. There is nothing more I can teach you. Now go, and may Altana smile upon you.
        WHAT_OH_HELLO_CHILD_I_M_JUST_A                                       = 6849,  -- What? Oh... Hello, child. I'm just a feeble old man. Go and leave me be.
        SO_LITTLE_BOY_GIRL_YOU_WANT_TO_BE                                    = 6850,  -- So, little boy/girl], you want to be an adventurer, do you? Well, you've got a long way to go, I reckon.
        I_AM_GLAD_THAT_YOU_SEEK_MY_WISDOM                                    = 6851,  -- I am glad that you seek my wisdom, child, but still you are too callow.
        I_TOO_ONCE_TOOK_UP_ARMS_FOR_HONOR                                    = 6852,  -- I, too, once took up arms for honor and country. But it was all in vain.
        I_HELPED_DEFEND_THE_NATION_I_TASTED_GLORY                            = 6853,  -- I helped defend the nation. I tasted glory. But behind their smiles people grew jealous. I lost my family, and my comrades deserted me.
        SOON_I_REALIZED_THAT_ALL_I_DID_EVERYTHING                            = 6854,  -- Soon I realized that all I did, everything I fought for was in vain. I left the ranks for good.
        BUT_OF_LATE_THE_BEASTMEN_RISE_IN_CHALLENGE                           = 6855,  -- But of late the beastmen rise in challenge. Again, many may lose dear friends and family to the storms of war.
        I_THOUGHT_THEN_OF_PREVENTING_SUCH_TRAGEDY_FROM                       = 6856,  -- I thought then of preventing such tragedy from happening again. Fortunately, an answer came to me.
        I_DECIDED_TO_TEACH_MY_SURVIVAL_TECHNIQUES_TO                         = 6857,  -- I decided to teach my survival techniques to brave youths like yourself.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_LEARN_THEM_YOU_MUST                                   = 6858,  -- If you wish to learn them, you must prove your worthiness to me.
        ARE_YOU_READY_YOU_BET_NOT_NOW                                        = 6859,  -- Are you ready? You bet. Not now.
        VERY_WELL_FIRST_BRING_ME_I_SHALL_WAIT                                = 6860,  -- Very well. First, bring me %. I shall wait here.
        WOULD_BE_FINE_TOO_IF_YOU_CAN_FIND                                    = 6861,  -- % would be fine, too...if you can find one.
        I_SEE                                                                = 6862,  -- I see.
        WELL_HAVE_YOU_FOUND                                                  = 6863,  -- Well? Have you found %?
        YES_THIS_WILL_DO_I_NEXT_DESIRE                                       = 6864,  -- Yes, this will do. I next desire %.
        WELL_DONE_NOW_FOR_YOUR_FINAL_TEST_BRING                              = 6865,  -- Well done! Now for your final test. Bring me %. Then you will gain what you desire.
        SPLENDID_AS_PROMISED_I_WILL_NOW_INSTRUCT_YOU                         = 6866,  -- Splendid. As promised, I will now instruct you in a most precious skill. I call it a support job. Listen well to learn its secrets.
        SUPPORT_JOBS_ARE_UNDERTAKEN_ANYWHERE_YOU_NORMALLY_CHANGE             = 6867,  -- Support jobs are undertaken anywhere you normally change jobs. And you must already be proficient in a job before you can declare it your support job.
        FURTHERMORE_THE_EFFECTIVE_LEVEL_OF_YOUR_SUPPORT_JOB                  = 6868,  -- Furthermore, the effective level of your support job can never exceed half that of your main job. Also, since it is merely a support job, you'll never advance through experience.
        I_SHALL_GIVE_AN_EXAMPLE_LET_US_SAY                                   = 6869,  -- I shall give an example. Let us say you have attained level 20 as a warrior and level 10 as a white mage. You would obviously declare your main job warrior, and your support job white mage.
        IN_THIS_EXAMPLE_YOU_FIGHT_AS_A_WARRIOR                               = 6870,  -- In this example, you fight as a warrior of 20 levels and as a white mage 10 levels lower. Thus, you would be performing both jobs to their maximum potential.
        IN_CONTRAST_IF_YOU_HAD_DECLARED_WHITE_MAGE                           = 6871,  -- In contrast, if you had declared white mage your main job and warrior your support job, things would be very different!
        SINCE_YOU_WOULD_HAVE_ONLY_10_LEVELS_OF                               = 6872,  -- Since you would have only 10 levels of experience as a white mage, your potential as a warrior would be reduced to half that of your main job. Thus, 5! Not a wise decision, is it?
        SIMILARLY_YOU_WOULDN_T_WANT_TO_MAKE_YOUR                             = 6873,  -- Similarly, you wouldn't want to make your support job something you've never done before. If your support job level is less than half that of your main job, your undeveloped skills would make not a difference. Remember this well!
        I_RECOMMEND_YOU_CHOOSE_A_SUPPORT_JOB_THAT                            = 6874,  -- I recommend you choose a support job that covers your main job's weaknesses, or one that enhances its strengths.
        I_REALIZE_THERE_IS_MUCH_TO_REMEMBER_MY                               = 6875,  -- I realize there is much to remember, my pupil.
        DO_YOU_UNDERSTAND_ALL_THAT_I_HAVE_TOLD                               = 6876,  -- Do you understand all that I have told you? Yes, I'm ready to go. Once more, please.
        VERY_GOOD_NOW_TRY_YOUR_HAND_AT_A                                     = 6877,  -- Very good. Now, try your hand at a support job. You'll find it helpful in your journeys, I'm sure.
        YOU_CAN_NOW_DESIGNATE_A_SUPPORT_JOB                                  = 6878,  -- You can now designate a support job.
        HEY_MISTER_LADY_I_KNOW_A_QUICK_AND                                   = 6879,  -- Hey mister/lady], I know a quick and easy way to make money, but you can't handle it yet.
        HEY_MISTER_LADY_YOU_GOT_SOME_SPARE_TIME                              = 6880,  -- Hey mister/lady], you got some spare time? I know the road to easy money! Want to give it a try?
        INTERESTED_YEAH_SO_FAR_NO_WAY                                        = 6881,  -- Interested? Yeah, so far. No way.
        AW_GIVE_ME_THE_COLD_SHOULDER_WILL_YOU                                = 6882,  -- Aw, give me the cold shoulder, will you? Well, you'll change your mind sooner or later, heheh.
        THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT_YOU_VE_JUST_GOT                                    = 6883,  -- That's the spirit! You've just got to prove yourself, that's all. Find some loot I hid in Davoi, bring it to me, and you win.
        BUT_THAT_S_NOT_ALL_BIG_SHOT_SWEETHEART                               = 6884,  -- But that's not all, big shot/sweetheart]. You'll get cold, hard cash! You can pick how much time you think you'll need to do the job.
        YOU_LL_HAVE_POCKETS_FULL_O_GIL_IF                                    = 6885,  -- You'll have pockets full o' gil if you bring it back before the time's up. If not...well, then you don't get jack! Simple, ain't it?
        YOU_WANT_MORE_SPENDING_MONEY_RIGHT_COME_ON                           = 6886,  -- You want more spending money, right? Come on, give it a try! You can't afford not to!
        GIVE_IT_A_TRY_I_M_GAME_I                                             = 6887,  -- Give it a try? I'm game. I'll pass, thanks.
        OKAY_WHATEVER_BUT_YOU_LL_NEVER_MAKE_THE                              = 6888,  -- Okay, whatever. But you'll never make the big time with that attitude. Prudes like you should stick to sellin' % to make ends meet.
        THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT_LIFE_S_NOTHIN_BUT                                  = 6889,  -- That's the spirit! Life's nothin' but a game of chance, right? Here's the rules.
        YOU_GOTTA_BRING_ME_HIDDEN_INSIDE_AN_URN                              = 6890,  -- You gotta bring me %, hidden inside an urn in Davoi. And I ain't tellin' ya which one.
        BUT_HERE_S_A_HINT_IT_S_IN                                            = 6891,  -- But here's a hint: It's in an urn all by itself, not one that's bunched up with others. Eh, you'll figure it out once you get there.
        BETS_START_AT_100_GIL_IT_GOES_100                                    = 6892,  -- Bets start at 100 gil! It goes 100, 250, 500, and the big 1000. Then choose a deadline of 24, 36, 48, 60, or 72 hours.
